ll/upwell over\n1-2 inertial time periods, after which an adjustment follows with a\nsub-inertial time scale. The dispersion characteristics of the submesoscale\nturbulent currents using single- and pair-particle statistics have been\ninvestigated. The shape change in clusters of four particles reveals\ndeformation into thin, needle-like structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Nov 2020 01:47:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-18"}
