, we confirm previous analytic\nscaling relations with our numerical models.\n  Conclusions. We warn against uncritically relying on transitions, which are\nstrongly affected by direct or indirect line-overlap effects. The predicted\nUV-continuum depression for the coolest grid-models needs to be checked, both\nobservationally, and regarding the underlying atomic data. Wind lines from\n\"super-ionized\" ions such as OVI can, in principle, be used to constrain the\ndistribution of wind-embedded shocks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Nov 2020 14:28:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-05"}
